# Riemann hypotesis (RH)

$$
\text{RH} \Leftrightarrow \pi(x) = \text{li}(x) + O_E(x^{\frac{1}{2}+\epsilon})
$$

$$
\text{RH} \equiv |\pi(x)-\text{li}(x)| < \frac{\sqrt{x}\log x}{8\pi}
$$, for all $x\geq 2657$

$$\text{RH} \Leftrightarrow M(n) = O(x^{\frac{1}{2} + \epsilon}) \forall \epsilon > 0,
\epsilon < 0.5$$

$$\text{RH} \equiv |M(n)| \leq c \cdot n^{\frac{1}{2}}$$
for any fixed $c$.

$$-1.229 < \text{lim sup}\frac{M(x)}{\sqrt{x}} < 1.218$$

Mertens function $M(n)$ is the count of square-free integer
up to $n$ that have an even number of prime factors, minus
the count of those that have an odd number.

$$M(n) = \sum_{k=1}^n \mu(k)$$, $\mu(k)$ is the Möbius function.

The determinant of the order $n$ Redheffer matrix is equal to $M(n)$.

