Let
$$ H_n = \sum_{j=1}^n \frac{1}{j}$$.
Show that, for each $n ≥ 1$,

$$
\sum_{d|n}d ≤ H_n + \exp(H_n)\log(H_n)
$$
, with equality only for $n = 1$.  The function $σ(n) = \sum_{d|n} d$ is the
sum of divisors function, so for example σ(6) = 12. The number $H_n$ is called
the n-th harmonic number.

This is equivalent to the Riemann hypothesis.

